<i>adverb</i>: 철석같이 [철썩까치], 의연히 [의연히], 불같이 [불가치], 분연히 [부ː년히], 뚝 [뚝], 딱 [딱], 결연히 [겨련히] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>철석같이 [철썩까치]</dt><br>
<dd>firmly; unwaveringly; resolutely</dd><br>
<dd>마음이나 의지, 약속 등이 쇠와 돌처럼 매우 굳고 단단하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's mind, will, word, etc., being very firm and steadfast just like iron and stone.</dd><br>
<dt>의연히 [의연히]</dt><br>
<dd>resolutely; firmly; unwaveringly</dd><br>
<dd>의지가 굳세어서 어떤 상황에서도 끄떡없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without being daunted under any circumstances because one's will is strong.</dd><br>
<dt>불같이 [불가치]</dt><br>
<dd>1. resolutely; passionately</dd><br>
<dd>신념이 굳고 감정이 매우 열정적이게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a firm belief and passion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. angrily</dd><br>
<dd>성격이 매우 급하고 사납게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very hurriedly and angrily.</dd><br>
<dd>3. fiercely; harshly</dd><br>
<dd>일어나거나 다그치는 기세가 세차고 무섭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a strong and scary situation in which something rises or one is pressed.</dd><br>
<dt>분연히 [부ː년히]</dt><br>
<dd>resolutely; vigorously</dd><br>
<dd>떨쳐 일어서는 기운이 세차고 꿋꿋하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a strong and indomitable spirit of overcoming difficulties.</dd><br>
<dt>뚝 [뚝]</dt><br>
<dd>1. all of a sudden; abruptly</dd><br>
<dd>계속되던 것이 갑자기 그치는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that something stops suddenly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. resolutely</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동 등을 매우 단호하고 명확하게 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking or behaving very firmly and definitely.</dd><br>
<dd>3. completely</dd><br>
<dd>다 쓰고 하나도 없는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something having been completely used up.</dd><br>
<dd>4. drastically; remarkably</dd><br>
<dd>성적이나 순위 등이 눈에 띄게 떨어지거나 정도가 약해지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that a grade, ranking, etc., falls or a degree gets weak very conspicuously.</dd><br>
<dd>5. considerably far away</dd><br>
<dd>거리가 꽤 떨어져 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>Being located quite distantly.</dd><br>
<dt>딱 [딱]</dt><br>
<dd>1. suddenly; all of a sudden</dd><br>
<dd>계속되던 소리, 생각, 행동이 갑자기 멈추거나 그치는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that an incessant noise, thought, or behavior suddenly stops or comes to a halt.</dd><br>
<dd>2. resolutely; decisively; flatly; completely; once and for all</dd><br>
<dd>아주 단호하게 끊거나 과감하게 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of one quitting something decisively or acting boldly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. really</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 마음에 들지 않는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of one hating something.</dd><br>
<dt>결연히 [겨련히]</dt><br>
<dd>resolutely; determinedly</dd><br>
<dd>매우 확고한 마음가짐과 태도로.</dd><br>
<dd>With a very resolute mind and attitude.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>